snippet: Richard Dare, the president of the New Jersey Symphony, resigned after nine days when questions arose over a past criminal case and over his business experience.
abstract: Richard Dare, new president of the New Jersey Symphony, resigns after only nine days when questions arise over a past criminal case and over aspects of his resume and business accomplishments.

byline.contributor: Lisa Schwartz in New York and Hiroko Tabuchi in Tokyo contributed additional reporting.

lead_paragraph: Richard Dare, the president of the New Jersey Symphony, resigned after nine days when questions arose over a past criminal case and over his business experience.

headline.seo: New Jersey Symphony President Richard Dare Quits
headline.main: New Jersey Symphony President Quits After Questions on His Past
